## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent challenges in measuring the direct impact of social media on domestic terrorism. Additionally, the evolving nature of social media platforms and their policies means that findings may quickly become outdated. Further research is needed to explore the effectiveness of current countermeasures and the role of emerging platforms in this context.

